[b]TVO - The Agenda with Steve Paikin, January 12 2009: The Male and Female Brain[/b]

Men, women and the brain. Part 1 of Mysteries of the Mind Week.

[u]The Debate: The Male and Female Brain[/u]

Hard wiring and social expectations: men, women, grey matter ... and even greyer zones.

[u]Guests:[/u]

[b]Michael Gurian[/b] is a consultant, author, and co-founder of The Gurian Institute.

[b]Margaret McCarthy[/b] is a professor of physiology at the University of Maryland School of Medicine.

[b]Susan Pinker[/b] is a developmental psychologist, journalist, and author of [i]The Sexual Paradox[/i]. For more information, visit [url=http://www.susanpinker.com/]susanpinker.com[/url].

